I just watched Batman: The Dark Knight on tv. It reminded me of what an awesome movies it is. It inspired me to make a list of movies that I want to own. 

So here goes: Batman Begins, Batman: The Dark Knight, all Pixar movies, O Brother Where Art Thou, Spiderman 1&2, Ironman 1&2, Sweeney Todd, Transformers 1&2, Lord of the Rings series, Rodger Rabbit, 300, King Arthur, Troy, League of Extraordinary Gentlemen, Phantom of the Opera, Public Enemies, The Simpson's Movie, The Spongebob Movie, Great Outdoors, Monty Python Holy Grail and Meaning of Life, Green Hornet (when it comes out)

And just so you know, here's a list of movies that I like and we have: Pride and Prejudice, Sense and Sensibility, Wolfman, Ghost Rider, Zombieland, Fantastic Mr. Fox, Alice in Wonderland, the Pirates of the Caribbean trilogy, Elf, Fantasia, and Fantasia 2000 

If you noticed any good movies that I missed and think should be on the list then comment with your additions and I'll think about it. That is, of course, if anyone is still bothering to read this. No one else has posted in a super long time.
 
On a side note. I remember the time when listing stuff in a sentence how before the last item you were supposed to use a comma and the word 'and'. Now it's socially acceptable to just use the 'and' without the comma, which bugs the crap outta me, but I'm trying to comply.

And on another side note, I've really gotten into some of the anime stuff on Adult Swim, especially InuYasha. I've watched all of the episodes and the 4th movie on Hulu.com. I've also read a lot of fanfics online. I'm only slightly obsessed. I'm debating on how I'm going to watch the first 3 movies. They weren't on the instant Netflix, but I could rejoin for a month or 2 so I could watch them without having to buy the darn things. I guess it depends on how much I could find them for on Amazon. I don't know if I could watch them and get all 3 back in just one month, so if I could get all three for under $20 then I might go ahead with it. I don't know.

So, married life is interesting, well, at least the hours are. We're on day shifts for now, so we have to get up around 3 AM. Danny gets home at 6ish PM and we go to bed around 8 PM. Well, I got on LJ to update my status when I saw that my user pics hadn't been changed in a while. So I did that, but halfway through I started getting error messages while trying to upload new pics. So now I'm annoyed with LJ and don't really feel like posting now. But I'm going to keep going anyways since I'm tired of seeing my pre-wedding post. Before the wedding I was watching a lot of wedding shows like Say Yes to the Dress and such but now that the wedding is over I have no patience for that kind of stuff.

OH MAN!!! There's this show on Animal Planet called Fatal Attractions that I absolutely LOVE!!! It's about people who own dangerous wild animals and keep them as pets when the animals turn on the owners and attack. Anyways the new season is coming out the 8th of October. So, I'm excited.

So I got a new phone and have unlimited texting now so that's cool. So if you have texting and want to talk then that's cool. If you have texting and don't know my number and want to text then write me a message on facebook and I'll give you my number or whatever. 

So, what's up? Not much here, just waiting for my laundry to get done so I can put it away and then maybe take a nap. I like naps. Especially with the whole getting up at 3AM thing. On the night shifts I rarely need a nap since I'm more nocturnal anyways. So getting up at 3 PM and going to bed around 8 AM doesn't bother me as much as 3AM and 8PM. Ug, I guess I'll go check the laundry. Peace out yo!

So a couple weeks ago my sister, dad, and I were watching this show on the Discovery Channel about the Bermuda Triangle. These scientists and theoretical physicists were theorizing why all those disappearances have happened and stuff. 

The scientists were saying that the boats and ships were disappearing because of rogue wave which are caused by two sets of waves converging from opposite sides of the island. These waves are about 50 times the size of regular waves and can occur in any weather condition.

Then the show discussed the disappearance of 5 navy planes over the bermuda triangle in 1945. These planes had 2 types of navigation and it wasn't supposed to be possible for them both to fail: but they did. Evidently that same day 3 or 4 communications towers had sighted 5 unidentified planes directly over Florida well before those 5 planes should have shown up; however, they were on the same flight path as the missing ones had last been. They theorized that those were the same planes and they had been lost, ran out of fuel, and subsequently crashed in a government restricted swamp in Georgia.

A recreational pilot in the 1980's had a unique ordeal when he flew through the triangle. As he was flying, the weather got worse and fog and clouds had started to obliterate his view; so he headed toward a tunnel he had spotted. When he entered the tunnel, it appeared to be about 10 miles long. Odd things started to happen. All of his electrical components failed along with his other magnetic form of navigation and he noticed the clouds had turned an odd shade of yellow with a dark spiral lining the entire length of the tunnel. About 20 seconds later he was out and in open skies. Most of his electrical equipment was still malfunctioning along with his navigation systems. His radio was now operational so he called the nearest ground control to find his location. He then learned he was flying over Florida. He was dumbfounded to learn he had flown about 300 hundred miles in about 20 seconds. His small aircraft was only supposed to go around 200mph at maximum, however this new information meant he had flown about 2000mph. 

The theoretical physicists had speculated that black energy had created a time warp and that this pilot had flown through it. They explained that black energy is pretty much like gravity
except that it pushes instead of pulls. and that the combination of gravity and black energy had caused a ripple in time allowing him to travel the same distance in an extremely short amount of time. They explained how this black energy occurred, but I don't remember what they said.

The pilot was confounded and by his experience and researched the experiences of other pilots that had went through the triangle. He had found a book that talked of another pilots experience that exactly duplicated his own. The book was published in the 70's however the pilot had experienced it in the 40's or 50's but didn't want to sound crazy so he didn't admit his experience until much later.

Anyways, the show was called Bermuda Triangle Exposed and is replaying on March 25th at 8 and 11PM on the Discovery Channel. I encourage you to watch it for yourselves. IT IS AMAZING!!!

You know how sometimes you do stuff that you probably shouldn't be doing but you're stubborn and decide to say "Screw it I'm an idiot I'll do it anyways." Well, this is one of those kinds of things. Listeneing to Pink Floyd at about 4:30 in the morning and dare I say blogging. Technically I guess this is blogging, but it just doesn't seem legit enough to call it blogging. Maybe flauxgging would be better...like faux blogging? I really don't know...about anything really. That's why this isn't really a good idea. Cuz I'll just end up talking about nothing and then peole will look at me until I stop talking and when I stop talking they will start talking again.........

If you are still reading you really need to reevaluate your priorities and maybe also the use of your time. You really wouldn't be missing much if you didn't read anymore. I won't be saying much of anything. Definitely nothing important. Besides how much I love tacos. And chocolate...and pretty much anything with sugar. 

I love Brain Damage by Pink Floyd...it's kinda creepy and yet awesome in a really messed up kinda way.

So, I'm thinking about getting another piercing. I already have 4 in each ear, so I don't think I'll have room for anything non-cartilage. But my ear is too folded over at the top, so I'd have to get it about a third of the was down my ear. I think it would look weird to get both of them done though, and since it is a cartilage piercing, it'll hurt more than the usual flesh piercings.
If I don't want it later on in life I can just take the earring out and the hole will close up eventually. It's not expensive, only about $15-25 depending on the type of earring I choose. I usually don't have problems with infections, so I'm not worried about that. Hmmm...what do you guys think, should I go for it?

Enough about me...how have you been?

In a week and 2 days Danny and I will have been together for 3 years. Looking back on it, it doesn't seem like it's been that long. I've learned a lot about him and have even realized some interesting little quirks in my personality. The times have been good to us and have brought a good amount of joy but some anger, sorrow, and frustration also. This is of course to be expected. However, seeing as the love and happiness has far out-shown and outnumbered the not-so-pleasant times, I believe things are working out in our favor. I also feel that as long as we continue to communicate and work with one another we can maintain a strong and lasting relationship. 

There are a few things that concern me. As you may know, Danny's last year of school is well on its way, while I still have until the end of 2009 yet to go. Since we are in totally different fields I'm not sure how us both having a career (potentially in different parts of the country) will affect our future together. I shouldn't worry about this too much though because I believe that if we were meant to be together we will find a way to work around this... with the help of God of course. I am however still seeking the token that proves him serious about our future together, meaning an engagement ring. There is still plenty of time for this I keep telling myself, but I'm getting quite anxious with his graduation date continuing to draw near. In his defense however, I will say that in this little town in the middle of nowhere, he would have a difficult time finding one that would suit me. Also, even with the nice payments he had been receiving from his internship at the mine, he still had to pay for gas, school, and the continuous problems with his Blazer. All of this would certainly not help his situation and have the same effect on mine. 

I'm getting to the point in my life where I just want to start settling into a career, a marriage, and long and healthy life. I don't want to stay in school anymore, but I've come way too far to just quit. I want the next chapter in my life to begin. I'd give a lot to be able to curl up with him at the end of a long work day and just relax and talk and eventually fall asleep next to each other. I know it will be difficult perhaps even most of the way, but I believe that it will be worth it...he will be worth it.

You can't get them out of your mind but thinking of them makes you all the more lonely and the pain only drives deeper into your heart and sole until your sobbing from it. And still the relief of sleep is out of reach. So the only thing left to do is sit in a dark room and listen to meaningful love songs on the internet (the best ones seem to be country songs by the way). It's only after you've experienced this that you can understand my position at this moment.
